Yesterday was National Girls and Women in Sports Day but every female student-athlete deserves their story, success, and resilience to be acknowledged. As a woman in athletics, I am extremely honored to be apart of Clemson's #HearHerRoar Campaign. They empower female athletes to to become leaders in communities, industries, and personal relationships.

Join me in donating, via the link in my bio, to continue to support female student-athletes.

social_posts.post_text: off time in-season: will find me in the great outdoors & stealing dads dog

Bringing Sarah Howell’s energy on this play to our first game of the ACC Championship 
Clemson will play North Carolina on Thursday at 7:30 p.m.

As many of you may know, I graduated in three years at Clemson University with a degree in Construction Science and Management. With two years left of eligibility and having previously entered the portal, I have decided to hang my cleats up. This sport created many relationships, connections, and memories. Softball molded me into the person I am today. It refined my character, initiated my work ethic, and conditioned my mind. I’m beyond thankful for every opportunity God provided me through this sport. It created my unique story that I will share for a lifetime. It all started when Dad brought home my first bat and ended with putting on my Clemson jersey for the last time. Making this decision required a lot of patience and thought. However, I thank everyone who supported me and helped me through this journey. Moving forward, I am happily saying farewell to a sport I’ve played for 15 years. I am flipping a page to a new chapter in my book. I am now eagerly entering into the family construction business back home in Alabama.❤️
my new best friend, everyone meet Boone🫶🏼
